{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":489,"text":"Two years ago, I have to say there was no problem."},{"time":3458,"text":"Two years ago, I knew exactly \nwhat an icon looked like."},{"time":7516,"text":"It looks like this."},{"time":9871,"text":"Everybody's icon, but also the default position"},{"time":12700,"text":"of a curator of Italian Renaissance \npaintings, which I was then."},{"time":16523,"text":"And in a way, this is also another default selection."},{"time":20215,"text":"Leonardo da Vinci's exquisitely soulful image"},{"time":24762,"text":"of the \"Lady with an Ermine.\""},{"time":26062,"text":"And I use that word, soulful, deliberately."},{"time":28605,"text":"Or then there's this, or rather these:"},{"time":30988,"text":"the two versions of Leonardo's \"Virgin of the Rocks\""},{"time":33642,"text":"that were about to come together \nin London for the very first time."},{"time":37918,"text":"In the exhibition that I was then in \nthe absolute throes of organizing."},{"time":42102,"text":"I was literally up to my eyes in Leonardo,"},{"time":45539,"text":"and I had been for three years."},{"time":47357,"text":"So, he was occupying every part of my brain."},{"time":51779,"text":"Leonardo had taught me, during that three years,"},{"time":54620,"text":"about what a picture can do."},{"time":56468,"text":"About taking you from your own \nmaterial world into a spiritual world."},{"time":61786,"text":"He said, actually, that he believed \nthe job of the painter"},{"time":64677,"text":"was to paint everything that was visible \nand invisible in the universe."},{"time":69128,"text":"That's a huge task. And yet, \nsomehow he achieves it."},{"time":73125,"text":"He shows us, I think, the human soul."},{"time":75896,"text":"He shows us the capacity of ourselves"},{"time":80342,"text":"to move into a spiritual realm."},{"time":83770,"text":"To see a vision of the universe that's \nmore perfect than our own."},{"time":88298,"text":"To see God's own plan, in some sense."},{"time":91874,"text":"So this, in a sense, was really \nwhat I believed an icon was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95945,"text":"At about that time, I started talking to Tom Campbell,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99803,"text":"director here of the Metropolitan Museum,"},{"time":102354,"text":"about what my next move might be."},{"time":105678,"text":"The move, in fact, back to an earlier life,"},{"time":108449,"text":"one I'd begun at the British Museum,"},{"time":110407,"text":"back to the world of three dimensions --"},{"time":112926,"text":"of sculpture and of decorative arts --"},{"time":115158,"text":"to take over the department of European sculpture \nand decorative arts, here at the Met."},{"time":119376,"text":"But it was an incredibly busy time."},{"time":120816,"text":"All the conversations were done \nat very peculiar times of the day --"},{"time":124223,"text":"over the phone."},{"time":127136,"text":"In the end, I accepted the job"},{"time":129200,"text":"without actually having been here."},{"time":130573,"text":"Again, I'd been there a couple of years before,"},{"time":133125,"text":"but on that particular visit."},{"time":135637,"text":"So, it was just before the time that \nthe Leonardo show was due to open"},{"time":139729,"text":"when I finally made it back to the Met, to New York,"},{"time":143751,"text":"to see my new domain."},{"time":145207,"text":"To see what European sculpture \nand decorative arts looked like,"},{"time":149150,"text":"beyond those Renaissance collections \nwith which I was so already familiar."},{"time":153941,"text":"And I thought, on that very first day, \nI better tour the galleries."},{"time":156938,"text":"Fifty-seven of these galleries --"},{"time":158390,"text":"like 57 varieties of baked beans, I believe."},{"time":163246,"text":"I walked through and I started in my comfort zone\nin the Italian Renaissance."},{"time":169367,"text":"And then I moved gradually around,"},{"time":171288,"text":"feeling a little lost sometimes."},{"time":174390,"text":"My head, also still full of the Leonardo exhibition"},{"time":177443,"text":"that was about to open, and I came across this."},{"time":181465,"text":"And I thought to myself: What the hell have I done?"},{"time":189395,"text":"There was absolutely no connection in my mind"},{"time":192748,"text":"at all and, in fact, if there was any emotion going on,"},{"time":195847,"text":"it was a kind of repulsion."},{"time":198216,"text":"This object felt utterly and completely alien."},{"time":201454,"text":"Silly at a level that I hadn't yet \nunderstood silliness to be."},{"time":206917,"text":"And then it was made worse --"},{"time":209116,"text":"there were two of them."},{"time":210961,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":214100,"text":"So, I started thinking about why it was, in fact,"},{"time":217067,"text":"that I disliked this object so much."},{"time":219523,"text":"What was the anatomy of my distaste?"},{"time":223329,"text":"Well, so much gold, so vulgar."},{"time":226797,"text":"You know, so nouveau riche, frankly."},{"time":230651,"text":"Leonardo himself had preached \nagainst the use of gold,"},{"time":233564,"text":"so it was absolutely anathema at that moment."},{"time":236999,"text":"And then there's little pretty sprigs \nof flowers everywhere. (Laughter)"},{"time":242427,"text":"And finally, that pink. That damned pink."},{"time":245946,"text":"It's such an extraordinarily artificial color."},{"time":248842,"text":"I mean, it's a color that I can't think of \nanything that you actually see in nature,"},{"time":252370,"text":"that looks that shade."},{"time":255458,"text":"The object even has its own tutu. (Laughter)"},{"time":259198,"text":"This little flouncy, spangly, bottomy bit"},{"time":261558,"text":"that sits at the bottom of the vase."},{"time":263593,"text":"It reminded me, in an odd kind of way,"},{"time":265966,"text":"of my niece's fifth birthday party."},{"time":268065,"text":"Where all the little girls would come \neither as a princess or a fairy."},{"time":272587,"text":"There was one who would come as a fairy princess."},{"time":274468,"text":"You should have seen the looks."},{"time":276890,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":278583,"text":"And I realize that this object was in my mind,"},{"time":281925,"text":"born from the same mind, from the same womb,"},{"time":284865,"text":"practically, as Barbie Ballerina. (Laughter)"},{"time":290089,"text":"And then there's the elephants. (Laughter)"},{"time":293611,"text":"Those extraordinary elephants"},{"time":295757,"text":"with their little, sort of strange, sinister expressions"},{"time":298481,"text":"and Greta Garbo eyelashes, with \nthese golden tusks and so on."},{"time":303778,"text":"I realized this was an elephant that had"},{"time":305554,"text":"absolutely nothing to do with a majestic \nmarch across the Serengeti."},{"time":311287,"text":"It was a Dumbo nightmare. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":316782,"text":"But something more profound \nwas happening as well."},{"time":319628,"text":"These objects, it seemed to me,"},{"time":321057,"text":"were quintessentially the kind that I \nand my liberal left friends in London"},{"time":325366,"text":"had always seen as summing up"},{"time":327901,"text":"something deplorable about the French aristocracy"},{"time":330740,"text":"in the 18th century."},{"time":332912,"text":"The label had told me that these pieces were made"},{"time":335701,"text":"by the Sèvres Manufactory,"},{"time":338412,"text":"made of porcelain in the late 1750s,"},{"time":341637,"text":"and designed by a designer called \nJean-Claude Duplessis,"},{"time":344768,"text":"actually somebody of extraordinary distinction"},{"time":346964,"text":"as I later learned."},{"time":349441,"text":"But for me, they summed up a kind of,"},{"time":354249,"text":"that sort of sheer uselessness of the aristocracy"},{"time":357663,"text":"in the 18th century."},{"time":361136,"text":"I and my colleagues had always thought"},{"time":363602,"text":"that these objects, in way, summed up the idea of,"},{"time":366558,"text":"you know -- no wonder there was a revolution."},{"time":368922,"text":"Or, indeed, thank God there was a revolution."},{"time":373465,"text":"There was a sort of idea really, that,"},{"time":375224,"text":"if you owned a vase like this,"},{"time":377897,"text":"then there was really only one fate possible."},{"time":381621,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":385685,"text":"So, there I was -- in a sort of paroxysm of horror."},{"time":390349,"text":"But I took the job and I went \non looking at these vases."},{"time":394309,"text":"I sort of had to because they're \non a through route in the Met."},{"time":397840,"text":"So, almost anywhere I went, there they were."},{"time":400472,"text":"They had this kind of odd sort of fascination,"},{"time":403241,"text":"like a car accident."},{"time":406259,"text":"Where I couldn't stop looking."},{"time":408983,"text":"And as I did so, I started thinking:"},{"time":411205,"text":"Well, what are we actually looking at here?"},{"time":415733,"text":"And what I started with was understanding this"},{"time":419064,"text":"as really a supreme piece of design."},{"time":422616,"text":"It took me a little time."},{"time":423713,"text":"But, that tutu for example --"},{"time":425151,"text":"actually, this is a piece that \ndoes dance in its own way."},{"time":428273,"text":"It has an extraordinary lightness"},{"time":429915,"text":"and yet, it is also amazing balanced."},{"time":432430,"text":"It has these kinds of sculptural ingredients."},{"time":435905,"text":"And then the play between --"},{"time":437544,"text":"actually really quite carefully disposed \ncolor and gilding, and the sculptural surface,"},{"time":442156,"text":"is really rather remarkable."},{"time":444431,"text":"And then I realized that this piece went into the kiln"},{"time":447261,"text":"four times, at least four times \nin order to arrive at this."},{"time":450651,"text":"How many moments for accident can you think of"},{"time":453705,"text":"that could have happened to this piece?"},{"time":455209,"text":"And then remember, not just one, but two."},{"time":457771,"text":"So he's having to arrive at two exactly matched"},{"time":462036,"text":"vases of this kind."},{"time":464548,"text":"And then this question of uselessness."},{"time":465954,"text":"Well actually, the end of the trunks \nwere originally candle holders."},{"time":470913,"text":"So what you would have had \nwere candles on either side."},{"time":474663,"text":"Imagine that effect of candlelight on that surface."},{"time":477219,"text":"On the slightly uneven pink, on the beautiful gold."},{"time":479951,"text":"It would have glittered in an interior,"},{"time":482697,"text":"a little like a little firework."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485779,"text":"And at that point, actually, \na firework went off in my brain."},{"time":489431,"text":"Somebody reminded me that, that word 'fancy' --"},{"time":492266,"text":"which in a sense for me, encapsulated this object --"},{"time":495376,"text":"actually comes from the same \nroot as the word 'fantasy.'"},{"time":499422,"text":"And that what this object was just as much in a way,"},{"time":502038,"text":"in its own way, as a Leonardo da Vinci painting,"},{"time":504490,"text":"is a portal to somewhere else."},{"time":506697,"text":"This is an object of the imagination."},{"time":510892,"text":"If you think about the mad 18th-century \noperas of the time -- set in the Orient."},{"time":517721,"text":"If you think about divans and perhaps even \nopium-induced visions of pink elephants,"},{"time":524200,"text":"then at that point, this object starts to make sense."},{"time":527501,"text":"This is an object which is all about escapism."},{"time":531557,"text":"It's about an escapism that happens --"},{"time":534754,"text":"that the aristocracy in France sought"},{"time":536775,"text":"very deliberately"},{"time":538561,"text":"to distinguish themselves from ordinary people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543129,"text":"It's not an escapism that"},{"time":545093,"text":"we feel particularly happy with today, however."},{"time":548960,"text":"And again, going on thinking about this,"},{"time":551945,"text":"I realize that in a way we're all victims"},{"time":555119,"text":"of a certain kind of tyranny"},{"time":557130,"text":"of the triumph of modernism"},{"time":559151,"text":"whereby form and function in an object"},{"time":561877,"text":"have to follow one another, or are deemed to do so."},{"time":565282,"text":"And the extraneous ornament is seen as really,"},{"time":568246,"text":"essentially, criminal."},{"time":571266,"text":"It's a triumph, in a way, of bourgeois\nvalues rather than aristocratic ones."},{"time":574417,"text":"And that seems fine."},{"time":576240,"text":"Except for the fact that it becomes a kind of \nsequestration of imagination."},{"time":583697,"text":"So just as in the 20th century, so many people"},{"time":586387,"text":"had the idea that their faith"},{"time":588375,"text":"took place on the Sabbath day,"},{"time":591057,"text":"and the rest of their lives --"},{"time":592431,"text":"their lives of washing machines and orthodontics --"},{"time":596409,"text":"took place on another day."},{"time":598441,"text":"Then, I think we've started doing the same."},{"time":602209,"text":"We've allowed ourselves to"},{"time":605541,"text":"lead our fantasy lives in front of screens."},{"time":607898,"text":"In the dark of the cinema, with the\ntelevision in the corner of the room."},{"time":611880,"text":"We've eliminated, in a sense, that constant"},{"time":615958,"text":"of the imagination that these vases \nrepresented in people's lives."},{"time":620886,"text":"So maybe it's time we got this back a little."},{"time":624922,"text":"I think it's beginning to happen."},{"time":627272,"text":"In London, for example,"},{"time":628538,"text":"with these extraordinary buildings"},{"time":630687,"text":"that have been appearing over the last few years."},{"time":633678,"text":"Redolent, in a sense, of science fiction,"},{"time":636081,"text":"turning London into a kind of fantasy playground."},{"time":638195,"text":"It's actually amazing to look out of \na high building nowadays there."},{"time":643049,"text":"But even then, there's a resistance."},{"time":644853,"text":"London has called these buildings the \nGherkin, the Shard, the Walkie Talkie --"},{"time":649189,"text":"bringing these soaring buildings down to Earth."},{"time":652494,"text":"There's an idea that we don't want these"},{"time":656574,"text":"anxious-making, imaginative journeys \nto happen in our daily lives."},{"time":661435,"text":"I feel lucky in a way,"},{"time":664703,"text":"I've encountered this object."},{"time":667251,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":669692,"text":"I found him on the Internet when \nI was looking up a reference."},{"time":672994,"text":"And there he was."},{"time":675888,"text":"And unlike the pink elephant vase,"},{"time":679202,"text":"this was a kind of love at first sight."},{"time":681175,"text":"In fact, reader, I married him. I bought him."},{"time":684031,"text":"And he now adorns my office."},{"time":687895,"text":"He's a Staffordshire figure made \nin the middle of the 19th century."},{"time":691436,"text":"He represents the actor, Edmund Kean, \nplaying Shakespeare's Richard III."},{"time":696242,"text":"And it's based, actually, on a more \nelevated piece of porcelain."},{"time":698695,"text":"So I loved, on an art historical level,"},{"time":700849,"text":"I loved that layered quality that he has."},{"time":705509,"text":"But more than that, I love him."},{"time":708002,"text":"In a way that I think would have been impossible"},{"time":709680,"text":"without the pink Sèvres vase in my Leonardo days."},{"time":712292,"text":"I love his orange and pink breeches."},{"time":715509,"text":"I love the fact that he seems to be going off to war,"},{"time":718259,"text":"having just finished the washing up. (Laughter)"},{"time":722691,"text":"He seems also to have forgotten his sword."},{"time":725168,"text":"I love his pink little cheeks, his munchkin energy."},{"time":727787,"text":"In a way, he's become my sort of alter ego."},{"time":730978,"text":"He's, I hope, a little bit dignified,"},{"time":733279,"text":"but mostly rather vulgar. (Laughter)"},{"time":738453,"text":"And energetic, I hope, too."},{"time":741671,"text":"I let him into my life because the Sèvres\npink elephant vase allowed me to do so."},{"time":746826,"text":"And before that Leonardo,"},{"time":748394,"text":"I understood that this object could become \npart of a journey for me every day,"},{"time":753500,"text":"sitting in my office."},{"time":756245,"text":"I really hope that others, all of you,"},{"time":759234,"text":"visiting objects in the museum,"},{"time":760809,"text":"and taking them home and \nfinding them for yourselves,"},{"time":763263,"text":"will allow those objects to flourish \nin your imaginative lives."},{"time":767577,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":769130,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}